            "title": "Woodside Energy: 1P reserves 1,882.1 MMboe, 2P reserves 2,999.5 MMboe, 2C resources 5,795.7 MMboe. CEO pleased with portfolio growth.",
            "id": "73071967-1059-49a6-bdac-c0deb702119f",
            "description": "Woodside revealed today that as of the end of 2025, they had 1,882.1 million barrels of oil equivalent (MMboe) in remaining proved (1P) reserves, 2,999.5 MMboe in remaining proved plus probable (2P) reserves, and 5,795.7 MMboe in remaining 2C contingent resources. After factoring out divestments and production, proved reserves saw a rise of 134.1 MMboe, while proved plus probable reserves grew by 141.0 MMboe. Acting CEO Liz Westcott noted this increase is due to another year of strong performance from the company's portfolio.",
